{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"4db7af65-711a-4e91-b585-13631db41159","content":"Use **`dotnet run`**, not `dotnet test`.\n\nThe `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HotReload` package works with the **Microsoft Testing Platform** (which your project opts into via `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport`). Hot reload is activated by running the test project as an executable:\n\n```bash\ndotnet run --project TestProject.csproj\n```\n\nWith the `TESTINGPLATFORM_HOTRELOAD_ENABLED` environment variable set, this will watch for file changes and re-run tests automatically. `dotnet test` does not support the hot reload workflow.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"7df704b3-0a42-4472-99f1-3460e3ab0a4c","outputTokens":139},"id":"4ee60950-88d2-4d0f-a098-10e4e7e4112e","timestamp":"2026-04-07T15:54:21.204Z","parentId":"d20d995f-f874-4feb-9157-715ebfc38bfb"}
